Between Linear Regression, Support Vector Machine (SVM) Regression, and Lasso Regression, Linear Regression had the best (lowest) RMSE (Root Mean Squared Error) for both the model that includes and does not include specific features ('inpatient_beds_used_covid', 'inpatient_bed_covid_utilization_numerator', and 'percent_of_inpatients_with_covid_numerator').

Lasso Regression with features RMSE: 31.990149647894203

Lasso Regression without features RMSE: 33.09643057612391

The increase from initial to final RMSE is minimal and most likely due to the model's generalization to new data.
